==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anapest
<hw>An"a*pest</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>anapaestus</ets>, Gr. <?/ an anapest, <it>i.e.</it>, a dactyl
reserved, or, as it were, <ets>struck back</ets>; fr. <?/;
<grk>'ana`</grk> back + <?/ to strike.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Pros.)</fld> <def>A metrical foot consisting of three syllables,
the first two short, or unaccented, the last long, or accented (⟦cre⟧
⟦cre⟧ -); the reverse of the <xex>dactyl</xex>. In Latin
<it>d⟦ecr⟧-⟦icr⟧-t⟦amac⟧s</it>, and in English
<it>in-ter-vene⟦bprime⟧</it>, are examples of anapests.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A verse composed of such feet.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anapestic</ent>⟦br⟧
